This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a supervised learning algorithm for fair and interpretable models. It also involves optimization of a multi-objective function, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it deals with decision-making systems and fairness issues. The topic of fairness in machine learning models is also relevant to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper's focus on interpretability may also place it under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), as interpretability is an important aspect of network analysis.
